      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry (coarse 1.2M, medium 3.1M, fine 7.8M cells). GCI-based discretization error estimated at 3.2% for the relative hemolysis index, meeting the 5% threshold at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must correspond to at least two of the five COU operating points within documented uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis data from Morrison et al. (2017) collected at 2500 RPM and 3500 RPM across three flow rates. Two of five COU operating points directly matched experimental conditions within ±5% flow rate and ±50 RPM. Temperature and fluid viscosity documented within acceptable range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted relative hemolysis index RH must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty at validated operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted RH values at matched operating points fell within experimental uncertainty bounds in 4 of 5 comparisons. Mean absolute error of 8.3% observed, consistent with MRL 2 expectations given the inherent variability in hemolysis measurement. Systematic over-prediction noted but conservative for safety assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
