      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in simulation (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) must directly correspond to the decision-relevant clinical outcome metric (RH < 1 criterion).",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the direct regulatory acceptance criterion per FDA guidance. CFD outputs of scalar shear stress integrated along particle trajectories are used to compute RH via the power-law hemolysis model. QoI relevance is high and directly tied to the acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
